						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 2) set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Mahishāsuramardinī temple.</p>						

						<p>Ballamahādēvī, 1277 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This indifferently engraved record registers a gift of money and land to goddess Bhagavatī of Niruvāra by the <hi rend="italic">sama[sta] pradhāna, dēśapurusha</hi> and other officials of this village.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1201, Īśvara, Kanyā 15, Sunday.</hi> The cyclic year Īśvara corresponds to Śaka 1199 when the other details regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">1277 A.D., September 12.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
